@startuml
title Optimisation Cancellation Flow

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam roundcorner 10
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam sequenceActorBackgroundColor #EEF2FF
skinparam sequenceActorBorderColor #4F46E5
skinparam noteBorderColor #A5B4FC
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #EEF2FF

actor "User / OEX /\nAuthorised Platform" as Caller
participant "OGW" as OGW
participant "OSB MS" as OSB
participant "NGW" as NGW
participant "OC MS" as OCMS
database "OC MS DB" as OCDB
queue "OC MS Outbox" as Outbox
queue "Kafka" as Kafka
participant "Python/Gurobi\nWorker" as Worker

== Cancellation Request ==

Caller -> OGW : 1. POST /optimisation/{id}/cancellation\n(If-Match header)
OGW -> OSB : 2-3. Invoke OSB MS\n<mTLS + User Context JWT>
OSB -> OSB : 4. Validate user context & runtime state\nExpose cancellation action only if allowed
OSB -> NGW : 5. Forward cancellation request\n<mTLS + OAuth2 (system-to-system)>
NGW -> OCMS : 6. Route cancellation request

== Validation ==

OCMS -> OCDB : 7. Validate ETag (If-Match)
OCDB --> OCMS : ETag confirmed
OCMS -> OCDB : 8. Check lifecycleStatus is\nACKNOWLEDGED, QUEUED, or PROCESSING
OCDB --> OCMS : Status eligible for cancellation

== State Transition & Event Publishing ==

OCMS -> OCDB : 9. Update lifecycleStatus = CANCELLING
OCDB --> OCMS : Confirmed
OCMS -> Outbox : 10. Write OptimisationRequestedEvent\n(instruction = CANCEL) — same transaction
Outbox -> Kafka : 11. Relay publishes event to Kafka

== Worker Cancellation ==

Kafka -> Worker : 12. Consume CANCEL instruction
Worker -> Worker : 13. Stop, cancel, or safely ignore\nwork where possible

== Final Projection ==

Worker -> Kafka : Publish cancellation outcome event
Kafka -> OCMS : Consume outcome
OCMS -> OCDB : 14. Project lifecycleStatus = CANCELLED\nwhen cancellation confirmed or safely resolved
note right of OCDB : Final state is eventual —\nworker determines safe resolution

@enduml
